            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/sd/press-centre/Press-releases/2010/invitation-to-tender-on-the-helicopter-r.html?id=612974" title="">
                        Invitation to tender on the helicopter route Værnes - Bodø
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Transport and Communications, 26.08.2010]</p>
                <p>The Norwegian Ministry of Transport and Communications invites airlines in all EAA countries to an open tender procedure for regional scheduled air services on the helicopter route Værnes – Bodø during the period 1 August 2011 to 31 July 2014. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/fin/press-center/Press-releases/2010/three-companies-excluded-from-the-govern.html?id=612790" title="">
                        Three companies excluded from the Government Pension Fund Global
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Finance, 23.08.2010]</p>
                <p>The Ministry of Finance has excluded two Israeli companies and one Malaysian company from the portfolio of the Government Pension Fund Global (GPFG).</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/Direct-peace-talks-between-Israel-and-the-Palestinians.html?id=612752" title="">
                        Direct peace talks between Israel and the Palestinians
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 20.08.2010]</p>
                <p>«I welcome the news that the US has invited Israel and the Palestinians to resume direct talks,» said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre. «Norway urges the parties to respond positively to the US invitation, and to seize this opportunity to make progress in the negotiations. This will put the peace process back on track.»</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/gavi_candidate.html?id=612352" title="">
                        Norwegian candidate for Chair of GAVI Alliance Board
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 13.08.2010]</p>
                <p>The Norwegian Government has nominated Dagfinn Høybråten (Member of the Storting and Leader of the Christian Democratic Party) as candidate for Chair of the Board of the GAVI Alliance.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/flood_support.html?id=612308" title="">
                        Norway to provide NOK 100 million to flood victims in Pakistan
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 12.08.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway is increasing its support for flood victims in Pakistan to NOK 100 million. The flood has affected 14 million people, six million of whom are in need of emergency food assistance. So far, 288.000 homes have been washed away.    </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/safe_mostafaei.html?id=612010" title="">
                        Foreign Minister Støre pleased that Mostafaei is safe
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 08.08.2010]</p>
                <p>“I am very pleased that human rights lawyer Mohammad Mostafaei is now safe in Norway,” said Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre.    </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/pakistan_flood.html?id=611896" title="">
                        Norway gives NOK 30 million to flood-ravaged Pakistan
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 03.08.2010]</p>
                <p>Pakistan is experiencing its worst floods in 80 years. According to the UN, over a million people are affected by the flooding, and reports suggest that almost 1100 people have lost their lives. “Norway is providing NOK 30 million to support emergency relief efforts during this critical phase,” Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre said.   </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/fkd/Press-Centre/Press-releases/2010/Ban-on-landings-of-mackerel-from-Faroese-and-Icelandic-vessels.html?id=611793" title="">
                        Ban on landings of mackerel from Faroese and Icelandic vessels
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Fisheries and Coastal Affairs, 29.07.2010]</p>
                <p>- The irresponsible fishing for mackerel which Iceland and the Faroe Islands have initiated as an attempt to secure future quota shares is a serious threat to the mackerel stock, and undermines the cooperation to secure the necessary conservation measures. I consider this situation very seriously, and it has been the topic of discussions between myself and the European Commissioner for Fisheries and Maritime Affairs, Norwegian Minister of Fisheries and Coastal Affairs Lisbeth Berg-Hansen says in a comment.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/eea-new.html?id=611778" title="">
                        New agreement on EEA financial mechanisms signed
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 28.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway and the EU have reached agreement on a financial contribution of close to NOK 15 billion for the period 2009–2014.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/Norway-welcomes-the-Advisory-Opinion-of-the-International-Court-of-Justice-in-the-Kosovo-Proceedings.html?id=611664" title="">
                        Norway welcomes the Advisory Opinion of the International Court of Justice in the Kosovo Proceedings
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 22.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway welcomes the clear advisory opinion delivered today by the International Court of Justice in The Hague on the question of the Accordance with International Law of the Unilateral Declaration of Independence by the Provisional Institutions of Self-Government of Kosovo (request for advisory opinion).</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/afghanistan.html?id=611478" title="">
                        Norwegian Foreign Minister visits Afghanistan 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 18.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Sunday 18 July was the first day of the Norwegian Foreign Minister’s visit to Afghanistan, during which he will visit the Norwegian forces in Northern Afghanistan and participate in the important International Conference on Afghanistan in Kabul.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/fd/press-centre/Press-releases/2010/norwegian-stockpiles-of-cluster-munition.html?id=611443" title="">
                        Norwegian stockpiles of cluster munitions are history
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Defence, 16.07.2010]</p>
                <p>On Friday the 16th of July at 2 p.m., the State Secretary for the Norwegian Ministry of Defence, Roger Ingebrigtsen, pushed the button to destroy Norway’s last batch of cluster munitions.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/terrorist_actions_uganda.html?id=611319" title="">
                        Norway condemns terrorist actions in Uganda
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 12.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway condemns the terrorist actions in Uganda’s capital, Kampala, where at least 74 innocent people were killed and many others injured on Sunday evening. Norwegian Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre commented: “We strongly condemn such terrorist actions.”</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/Norways-support-to-drought-victims-in-eastern-Sahel-increased-.html?id=611289" title="">
                        Norway’s support to drought victims in eastern Sahel increased 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 09.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Ten million people in eastern Sahel are affected by drought and food shortages. Norwegian Minister of Foreign Affairs Jonas Gahr Støre commented: “The situation is very serious for the population in this area. We have therefore decided to increase our support to NOK 50 million.”</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/cuba_prisoners.html?id=611241" title="">
                        Norway welcomes the release of political prisoners in Cuba 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 08.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norwegian Foreign Minister Jonas Gahr Støre commented: “Norway, together with the EU, has steadfastly demanded the unconditional release of political prisoners in Cuba. We were very pleased to receive the news today that the Cuban authorities will release 52 political prisoners.”</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/smk/press-center/Press-releases/2010/norwegian-prime-minister-says-terrorism-.html?id=611221" title="">
                        Suspected preparations to commit terrorist acts
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[The Office of the Prime Minister, 08.07.2010]</p>
                <p>The Norwegian Police Security Service (PST) has apprehended three individuals suspected of having prepared terrorist acts. “Terrorism creates fear and insecurity, and must be combated. We shall maintain and consolidate public security in Norway,” says Prime Minister Jens Stoltenberg.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/oed/press-center/Press-releases/2010/sdfi-values-of-865-billion-kroner-.html?id=611066" title="">
                        SDFI values of 865 billion kroner 
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Petroleum and Energy, 06.07.2010]</p>
                <p>The value of the State’s Direct Financial Interest (SDFI) as of 1 January 2010 is estimated at 865 billion kroner. This is the result of a valuation of the SDFI portfolio carried out by Wood Mackenzie on behalf of the Ministry of Petroleum and Energy. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/press/news/2010/presidency_cbss.html?id=610696" title="">
                        Norway takes over presidency of the Council of the Baltic Sea States
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 01.07.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway has taken over the presidency of the Council of the Baltic Sea States. This means that the Norwegian Foreign Minister will serve as president of the council for one year.  </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/smk/press-center/Press-releases/2010/state-secretary-to-leave-oed-for-hod.html?id=610253" title="">
                        State secretary to leave OED for HOD
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[The Office of the Prime Minister, 25.06.2010]</p>
                <p>In today’s session of the Council of State the King has honourably dismissed Mr. Robin Kåss from his office as state secretary to Minister of Petroleum and Energy Terje Riis-Johansen, and at the same time appointed him as state secretary to Minister of Health and Care Services Anne-Grete Strøm-Erichsen. </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/smk/press-center/Press-releases/2010/New-political-adviser.html?id=609553" title="">
                        New political adviser
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[The Office of the Prime Minister, 24.06.2010]</p>
                <p>The Office of the Prime Minister has from 25 June 2010 appointed Mr. Tord Dale (32), adviser, Oslo, as political adviser to Minister of Health and Care Services Anne-Grete Strøm-Erichsen.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/oed/press-center/Press-releases/2010/21th-Licensing-Round--Awards.html?id=609291" title="">
                         Announcement – 21st Licensing Round
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Petroleum and Energy, 23.06.2010]</p>
                <p>The Ministry of Petroleum and Energy hereby announces the 21st Licensing Round, which comprises 94 blocks or parts of blocks in the Norwegian Sea and the Barents Sea.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <hr class="seperator" />   
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/nhd/press-centre/Press-releases/2010-2/the-states-ownership-report-2009.html?id=609251" title="">
                        The State's Ownership Report 2009
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Ministry of Trade and Industry, 23.06.2010]</p>
                <p>- We have put behind us another demanding year for Norwegian business. In the midst of a global economic crisis, however, Norwegian companies have managed better than many dared to hope, Minister of Trade and Industry Trond Giske said.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
